<l>aiau veṉṉu māyī reḻuttiṟ</l>
<l>kikara vukara micainiṟai vākum</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The sound <foreign xml:lang="ta">i</foreign> and the sound <foreign xml:lang="ta">u</foreign> occur to supplement</l>
<l>the two phonemes <foreign xml:lang="ta">ai</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="ta">au.</foreign><note
              place="foot">
              <foreign xml:lang="ta">Iḷamp.</foreign> quotes only <foreign
                xml:lang="ta">aii</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="ta">auu</foreign> without giving concrete examples. Later commentators quote items like <foreign xml:lang="ta">ma<corr>ṉau</corr>kam</foreign> (the meaning of which is however unknown). For vowel clusters, see the
          comment on this Chapter.</note></l>
      </lg>
